item.description:
Due to the nature of the Tailwind CSS library there is no pre-built support for handling Markdown. Luckily, there is this GitHub repository iandinwoodie/github-markdown-tailwindcss that has implemented support for it.
Usage Add class markdown to the element that you want to style. With Hugo you can add this kind of snippet:
&lt;div class=&#34;markdown&#34;&gt; {{ .Content }} &lt;/div&gt;
